title: For Sale:  Mauser K98 German WWII made/used Serbian Capture/Marked
postcontent:
Mauser K98/48 (German Made- Serbian Capture), 8mm Mauser. Has Sarco/Germany import marks on barrel, which means it was probably a German Barrel and not original to the receiver, bore is shootable but I'd rate it less then 7/10 - so still plenty fine. No import marks on the receiver. Receiver has the Serbian Crest and Preduzece 44 marking, but the German K98 marking does not bear the /44 stamp meaning it was german produced and reworked in the late 1940s by the Serbs. Numbers mostly match through, but I think there is an odd ball one or two that are different - nothing significant. Bolt match's itself and the gun. There are Waffenamt markings (Wa 263 I believe) on the rear sight, but I suspect that's not from when the Serbs had it (they rarely left any of the german Markings). 

There is also an SS stamp and a deathhead mark on the barrel. I'm almost positive these were not original, and is typical of a Mitchell's Mauser or any number that had previous owners with a hammer and stamp (common in the 80s). Just letting you know they are there. Stock is solid. Includes nice re-production leather sling. 

Asking $325 FTF or shipped on your dime. Got it as part of a trade, wanted to get it out shooting, but haven't even had the time. Looking a move coming up so paring down. 

More photos available upon request. A few more here:
https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BxycAaaCakTldHpOVHBXYWZEdnM
